The paper deals with graph parameters and their computational complexity, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The use of randomized projections in the paper suggests that it may also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) category. The paper deals with geometric measures of graphs, which is a topic in Computational Geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the spread constant, which is a measure of graph connectivity, and the maximum variance embedding problem, which is a topic in Statistical Learning (cs.SI).
